        "is_draft": false,
        "status_summary": "The ASKDD Chatbot project has achieved 100% completion as of today, January 19, 2026, marking a successful conclusion ahead of the anticipated project timeline from December 1, 2025, to January 2, 2026. The team collaborated effectively throughout the lifecycle of the project, ensuring all delivery milestones were met on time and to the client\u2019s satisfaction.\n\nIn terms of team capacity, total allocations totaled 245%, with Henry playing a crucial role at 90% and a secondary allocation of 50%. Amrit contributed significantly as a QA Engineer with a 10% allocation, while Don, as a customer, provided 5% toward collaboration. Despite the high allocations, the team managed resources efficiently, ensuring a balanced workload. \n\nHowever, a medium-impact risk has been identified concerning the WhatsApp integration, specifically that it does not permit users to utilize WhatsApp Business alongside regular WhatsApp accounts. This may affect user experience; therefore, a strategy is required to address this concern proactively. Overall, the project is healthy, and the team is well-prepared to handle any emerging issues as we transition to post-launch support.",
